    "desc": "General Motors is home to Buick, Cadillac, GMC & Chevrolet. Learn about General Motor's rich history and dedication to community, sustainability, & innovation.",
    "navbar": "",
    "text": "everybody in.\nOur Ultium Platform brings flexibility, power and range. We’re making electric vehicles for all.\nSee How\nSimulated Battery1 and GMC Hummer EV2 shown.\nWe’re building today for a safe,\nmore sustainable tomorrow.\nVehicle Safety\nThrough research, technology, and advocacy we are advancing our vision of a future with zero crashes.\nLEARN MORE\nElectrification\nOur new Ultium Platform can help put everyone in an EV, bringing the world to an all-electric future.\nLEARN MORE\nSocial Impact\nWe are committed to becoming the most inclusive company in the world, and we won't stop until we get there.\nLEARN MORE\nShow truck shown. Actual production will vary. Model year 2024 Silverado EV available Fall 2023. Simulated energy product shown. Subject to change.\nGM Energy: Power when you need it\nWith GM Energy’s connected products and services, EV owners have more control over home energy management and expanded access to EV charging. Its tools and services are designed to offer a cohesive energy solution for home, commercial and EV customers—even helping to mitigate the effects of power outages in times of need. Explore GM Energy’s solutions for customers here.\nLearn More\nPreproduction model shown. Actual production model may vary. MY23 LYRIQ orders are full. Go to Cadillac.com for availability information.\nEV LIVE\nLearn about EVs from the comfort of home\nConnect with us on EV LIVE as we transition to an all-electric future. Live from our studio, chat with our EV specialists and get real-time answers to all your EV questions. Explore the latest GM EVs and all aspects of the EV experience, including ownership, maintenance, and home and public charging. No matter where you are on your EV journey, the experts at EV LIVE are here to help.\nLearn More\nSimulated, preproduction or concept products shown and subject to change. Certain products not currently available or subject to limited availability. See vehicle websites for details.\nElectrifying our lineup, one amazing vehicle at a time\n\nLearn More\n“Globally, one billion people experience some form of disability, and it's something that most of us will experience at some point in our lives. As we strive to become the most inclusive company in the world, it only makes sense that accessibility is a part of the equation.”\nCARRIE MORTON (She/Her) // Chief Engineer, Accessibility Center of Excellence\n  Join Our Team\nWe’re looking for adventure seekers and imaginative thought leaders to help us transform mobility and advance an all-electric future.\nExplore Opportunities\nLATEST STORIES\nSafely deploying hands-free driving\nREAD STORY\nThe inclusive message behind “everybody in”\nREAD STORY\nRoad-tripping From Detroit to New York City in a Bolt EUV\nREAD STORY\nThe soundtrack to your drive\nREAD STORY\nPowering up: Leading the charge for an EV infrastructure\nREAD STORY\nAll Stories\nFollow us and the future of transportation.\nENTERPRISE\nSERVICE AND PARTS\nCertified Service\nGM Genuine Parts & ACDelco\nChevrolet Performance Parts\nFINANCIAL\nMy Rewards\nGM Financial\nMy GM Rewards Card\nGM Business Card\nCorporate Offers\nPARTNERS\nDiversity Dealer Relations\nGlobal Connect\nMotors Holdings\nSupplyPower\nSupplier Diversity\nINDUSTRY SOLUTIONS\nGM Fleet\nGM Defense\nGM Ventures\nGM Powered Solutions\nUltium Cell\nMORE\nAlumni and Retirees\nGM Heritage\nElectric Vehicles Glossary\nOWNERS\nMy GM Account\nIgnition Updates\nRecall Center\nTakata Information\nSHOP\nChevrolet\nBuick\nGMC\nCadillac\nOnStar and Connected Services\nOnStar Insurance\nCertified Pre-Owned\nGM Company Store\nGM Parts Store\nLEGAL\nCopyright/Trademark\nPrivacy Statement\nSecurity Vulnerability Disclosure\nSocial Media Policy\nSupply Chain Responsibility\nTexting Policy\nUser Guidelines\nAccessibility\nYour Privacy Choices & Opt-Out Rights\n\n© General Motors\nContact Us Sitemap Global Sites",
